The model was based on discrete time periods (e.g., hourly analysis) to analyze choices of resources and performance, so it might overlook more abrupt or even smooth shifts in system behavior that would be exposed in a continuous-time model. Another constraint is that four human interventions (
H = 4
) are being drawn upon as required, and this might be too limiting to the flexibility and quick response that could be achieved in actual disaster response situations. Thus, the resilience predictions would appear slightly pessimistic relative to what might actually be achieved in Table 3.

